 <a href="https://github.com/facebook" rel="nofollow">https://github.com/facebook</a><p>Also I guess it would be hard to argue that Apple originated LLVM given its history:<p><a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/LLVM" rel="nofollow">http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/LLVM</a><p>And it looks like CUPS is not 100% open source:<p><a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/CUPS" rel="nofollow">http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/CUPS</a><p>Here&#x27;s an interesting article with some talking points.<p><a href="http://readwrite.com/2014/05/05/apple-github-ios-android-developers" rel="nofollow">http://readwrite.com/2014/05/05/apple-github-ios-android-dev...</a>
